match.strFilename: English Premier League 2020-09-12 Burnley vs Man United
English Premier League 2020-09-12 Man City vs Aston Villa
English Premier League 2020-09-12 Crystal Palace vs Southampton
match.strDescriptionEN: Crystal Palace and Southampton collide on the opening weekend of the new Premier League season. The two performed very differently after last season's restart, with Southampton one of the most in-form teams, while Palace lost seven of its last eight.

match.strFilename: English Premier League 2020-09-12 Fulham vs Arsenal
match.strDescriptionEN: Newly-promoted Fulham's Premier League adventure begins with a London derby against Arsenal at Craven Cottage. Mikel Arteta begins his first full season in charge of the Gunners and has bolstered his squad by signing Willian from Chelsea.
match.strAwayGoalDetails: 8: Alexander Lacazette;49: Gabriel Magalhães;57: Pierre-Emerick Aubameyang

match.strFilename: English Premier League 2020-09-12 Liverpool vs Leeds
match.strDescriptionEN: Leeds United faces a big test on its long-awaited return to the Premier League as it takes on defending champion, Liverpool. Jurgen Klopp's men are well-rested, unlike other title contenders, as they didn't play the UEFA Champions League in August.
match.strHomeGoalDetails: 4: Mohamed Salah (PG);20: Virgil van Dijk;33: Mohamed Salah;88: Mohamed Salah (PG);
match.strAwayGoalDetails: 12: Jack Harrison;30: Patrick Bamford;66: Mateusz Klich;

match.strFilename: English Premier League 2020-09-12 West Ham vs Newcastle
match.strDescriptionEN: After spending much of last season battling relegation, West Ham United and Newcastle United begin the new season in search of a fresh start. The Magpies continue life under long-term owner Mike Ashley after their proposed offseason sale fell through.

match.strFilename: English Premier League 2020-09-13 Tottenham vs Everton
match.strDescriptionEN: Two titans of world soccer collide on the opening weekend as Jose Mourinho's Tottenham Hotspur takes on Carlo Ancelotti's Everton. Spurs striker Harry Kane has an impressive record against Everton, scoring nine goals in 10 games.

match.strFilename: English Premier League 2020-09-13 West Brom vs Leicester
match.strDescriptionEN: Reigning Premier League Golden Boot winner Jamie Vardy looks to make a fast start to the season as Leicester City heads on the road to face newly-promoted West Bromwich Albion. The Foxes are aiming to build on last season's superb 5th-place finish.
match.strAwayGoalDetails: 56: Timothy Castagne;74: Jamie Vardy (PG);84: Jamie Vardy (PG)

match.strFilename: English Premier League 2020-09-14 Brighton vs Chelsea
match.strDescriptionEN: Graham Potter’s Brighton and Hove Albion avoided relegation last season with a steely resilience to not be beaten. Such durability was showcased against Chelsea at AMEX Stadium as Alireza Jahanbakhsh’s bicycle kick secured a point for the Seagulls.

match.strFilename: English Premier League 2020-09-14 Sheffield United vs Wolves
match.strDescriptionEN: Sheffield United and Wolverhampton Wanderers begin their season by going head-to-head at Bramall Lane. Both teams were in the hunt for European qualification for most of last season but missed out after falling away in the final couple of weeks.

match.strFilename: English Premier League 2020-09-19 Everton vs West Brom
match.strDescriptionEN: Everton faces newly-promoted West Bromwich Albion at Goodison Park. After a disappointing 12th-place finish last season, Carlo Ancelotti will be looking to get his team back in the top half of tha table and secure a European qualification spot.
match.strHomeGoalDetails: 31: Dominic Calvert-Lewin;45: James Rodriguez;54: Michael Keane;62: Dominic Calvert-Lewin;66: Dominic Calvert-Lewin

match.strHomeGoalDetails: 5: Hélder Costa;41: Mateusz Klich (PG);50: Patrick Bamford;57: Hélder Costa
match.strAwayGoalDetails: 34: Aleksandar Mitrović;62: Bobby De Cordova-Reid;67: Aleksandar Mitrović

match.strFilename: English Premier League 2020-09-19 Man United vs Crystal Palace
match.strDescriptionEN: Manchester United gets its 2020/21 Premier League campaign underway against Crystal Palace at Old Trafford. The Red Devils have bolstered their ranks during the transfer window with the signing of Dutch midfielder Donny van de Beek.
match.strHomeGoalDetails: 7: Andros Townsend;74: Wilfred Zaha;85: Wilfred Zaha

match.strFilename: English Premier League 2020-09-19 Arsenal vs West Ham
match.strDescriptionEN: An all-London clash at Emirates Stadium as Arsenal hosts West Ham United. Gunners boss Mikel Arteta is looking to build on a successful first nine months in charge, which saw his team win the FA Cup and Community Shield in the last two months.

match.strFilename: English Premier League 2020-09-20 Chelsea vs Liverpool
match.strDescriptionEN: Liverpool heads on the road to face Chelsea in the first major test of its Premier League title defence. Its trophy presentation last season took place after a gripping 5-3 victory over Chelsea, which included a goal from Christian Pulisic.

match.strFilename: English Premier League 2020-09-20 Leicester vs Burnley
match.strDescriptionEN: Burnley travels to Leicester City in the first away game of its 2020/21 Premier League campaign. Sean Dyche's team finished 10th last season and will be looking to challenge for a UEFA Europa League spot this time around.
match.strHomeGoalDetails: 20: Harvey Barnes;50: Erik Pieters (OG);61: James Justin;79: Dennis Praet

match.strFilename: English Premier League 2020-09-20 Newcastle vs Brighton
match.strDescriptionEN: Brighton and Hove Albion makes the long trip to the north of England to face Newcastle United at St. James' Park. New signings Callum Wilson and Jeff Hendrick have hit the ground running for Newcastle, both scoring on matchday one.
match.strAwayGoalDetails: 4: Neal Maupay (PG);7: Neal Maupay;83: Aaron Connolly

match.strFilename: English Premier League 2020-09-20 Southampton vs Tottenham
match.strDescriptionEN: Southampton welcomes Jose Mourinho's Tottenham Hotspur to St Mary's Stadium. Saints fans will hope that star striker Danny Ings can replicate his form from last season, which saw him finish second in the race for the Premier League Golden Boot.

match.strFilename: English Premier League 2020-09-21 Wolves vs Man City
match.strDescriptionEN: Manchester City's Premier League season finally gets underway as it takes on Wolverhampton Wanderers. City failed to beat Wolves in both matches last year, with the latter overcoming a two-goal deficit to win 3-2 in a thriller at Molineux.

match.strFilename: English Premier League 2020-09-21 Aston Villa vs Sheffield United
match.strDescriptionEN: After securing top-flight survival on the final day, Aston Villa begins its 2020/21 Premier League campaign against Sheffield United. The Blades are seeking revenge after goal-line technology robbed Chris Wilder's team of a win at Villa Park in July.

match.strFilename: English Premier League 2020-09-26 Brighton vs Man United
match.strDescriptionEN: Ole Gunnar Solskjaer's Manchester United heads on the road for the first time this Premier League season as it takes on Brighton and Hove Albion. Instrumental midfielder Bruno Fernandes scored a brace in a 3-0 win when United last visited in June.

match.strFilename: English Premier League 2020-09-26 Burnley vs Southampton
match.strDescriptionEN: Two English strikers come up against their former teams as Danny Ings' Southampton visits Jay Rodriguez's Burnley at Turf Moor. Ings scored one of his 22 Premier League goals last season against Burnley, as the Clarets won 2-1 at St Mary's.

match.strFilename: English Premier League 2020-09-26 Crystal Palace vs Everton
match.strDescriptionEN: Crystal Palace and Everton meet at Selhurst Park in the Premier League. Everton's midfield has been revamped over the summer, with the introduction of James Rodriguez, Allan and Abdoulaye Doucoure providing a new look to Carlo Ancelotti's team.

match.strFilename: English Premier League 2020-09-26 West Brom vs Chelsea
match.strDescriptionEN: The Hawthorns opens its doors to Chelsea as West Bromwich Albion continues to readjust to life back in the Premier League. Chelsea has a strong record at this ground, winning its last three matches here.

match.strFilename: English Premier League 2020-09-27 Man City vs Leicester
match.strDescriptionEN: Manchester City and Leicester City meet at Etihad Stadium. Since winning 3-1 here on the way to winning the Premier League, Leicester has lost all four times it has visited, with former star Riyad Mahrez scoring in last season's 3-1 result.

match.strFilename: English Premier League 2020-09-27 Sheffield United vs Leeds
match.strDescriptionEN: Pride is on the line in this Yorkshire Derby as Sheffield United hosts Leeds United. This is the first time that these two soccer teams have met in the Premier League since 1994, although they have met 12 times in other competitions since then.

match.strFilename: English Premier League 2020-09-27 Tottenham vs Newcastle
match.strDescriptionEN: Newcastle United visits Tottenham Hotspur Stadium a year since winning 1-0 on its first visit there. Newcastle signings Callum Wilson and Ryan Fraser were linked with Tottenham Hotspur in the summer - could they inspire a win for the Magpies?

match.strFilename: English Premier League 2020-09-27 West Ham vs Wolves
match.strDescriptionEN: Three months after winning 2-0 at London Stadium, Wolverhampton Wanderers return to East London aiming for a fifth-straight win over West Ham United. Since returning to the Premier League, Wolves has not conceded once to the Hammers.

match.strFilename: English Premier League 2020-09-28 Fulham vs Aston Villa
match.strDescriptionEN: Fulham and Aston Villa clash in the Premier League for the first time in six-and-a-half years. The pair did meet in the EFL Championship playoff final at the end of the 2017/18 season, with a Tom Cairney goal sealing a 1-0 win for Fulham.

match.strFilename: English Premier League 2020-09-28 Liverpool vs Arsenal
match.strDescriptionEN: Liverpool may be the current Premier League champion but it has already lost to Arsenal once this season, as the Gunners won the season-opening Community Shield back in August. Can Liverpool get its revenge as Mikel Arteta's men come to Anfield?

match.strFilename: English Premier League 2020-10-03 Chelsea vs Crystal Palace
match.strDescriptionEN: Chelsea and Crystal Palace clash in a London derby at Stamford Bridge. The host has strengthened in almost every area of the field over the summer, while the Eagles have finally spent some of the £50m they received for Aaron Wan-Bissaka in 2019.

match.strFilename: English Premier League 2020-10-03 Everton vs Brighton
match.strDescriptionEN: Everton, which has started the season brightly under Carlo Ancelotti, takes on Brighton & Hove Albion, whose manager Graham Potter has assembled a squad many consider capable of upsetting the odds this season.

match.strFilename: English Premier League 2020-10-03 Leeds vs Man City
match.strDescriptionEN: For the first time in 16 years, Leeds United welcomes Manchester City to Elland Road. This matchup will see Pep Guardiola and Marcelo Bielsa - two managers who have certainly left their mark on the beautiful game and each other - go head-to-head.

match.strFilename: English Premier League 2020-10-03 Newcastle vs Burnley
match.strDescriptionEN: Newcastle United and Burnley square off at St. James' Park, where the Magpies were humbled 3-0 by Brighton and Hove Albion in their home opener. Newcastle did bounce back from that defeat by thumping Morecambe 7-0 in the Carabao Cup, though.

match.strFilename: English Premier League 2020-10-04 Arsenal vs Sheffield United
match.strDescriptionEN: Chris Wilder's Sheffield United travels to north London to take on a rejuvenated Arsenal led by Mikel Arteta. In their first season back in the Premier League, the Blades took four points off Arsenal, including a 1-1 draw at Emirates Stadium.

match.strFilename: English Premier League 2020-10-04 Aston Villa vs Liverpool
match.strDescriptionEN: Aston Villa and Liverpool square off at Villa Park, where last season, these teams produced one of the most exciting finishes of the campaign, as Liverpool scored twice late on to overturn an early Trezeguet goal.

match.strFilename: English Premier League 2020-10-04 Leicester vs West Ham
match.strDescriptionEN: Leicester City hosts West Ham United at King Power Stadium as Brendan Rodgers' team looks to continue its good start to the season. The Hammers, meanwhile, are in the middle of an intimidating run of fixtures.

match.strFilename: English Premier League 2020-10-04 Man United vs Tottenham
match.strDescriptionEN: Tottenham Hotspur makes the trip to Old Trafford to take on Manchester United. Spurs has only beaten United once in its last four attempts, a 3-0 win at the ‘Theatre of Dreams’ when Jose Mourinho was in the opposing dugout.

match.strFilename: English Premier League 2020-10-04 Southampton vs West Brom
match.strDescriptionEN: Southampton welcomes West Bromwich Albion back to St. Mary's for the first time since October 2017, when Sofiane Boufal scored the only goal of the game as the Saints came out on top. Just three Southampton players remain from that starting line-up.

match.strFilename: English Premier League 2020-10-04 Wolves vs Fulham
match.strDescriptionEN: Wolverhampton Wanderers does battle with Fulham, which has made a rocky start to life back in the top flight. Nuno Espirito Santo, meanwhile, has continued to bolster his side with his compatriots, meaning Wolves now has 10 Portuguese players.

match.strFilename: English Premier League 2020-10-17 Chelsea vs Southampton
match.strDescriptionEN: Chelsea resumes its Premier League campaign with the arrival of Southampton in South West London. New signing Timo Werner continues to chase his first Premier League goal for the Blues, who beat Crystal Palace 4-0 last time out.

match.strFilename: English Premier League 2020-10-17 Everton vs Liverpool
match.strDescriptionEN: Fierce rivals Everton and Liverpool meet for the second behind-closed-doors Merseyside Derby, with the Toffees flying high at the top of the table alongside the Reds. Goodison Park hosted both teams' first game of Project Restart.

match.strFilename: English Premier League 2020-10-17 Man City vs Arsenal
match.strDescriptionEN: Mikel Arteta returns to Manchester City, targeting another victory over his former mentor Pep Guardiola, who he knocked out of last season’s FA Cup. Arsenal, however, does not enjoy playing at Etihad Stadium, having last won here in 2015.

match.strFilename: English Premier League 2020-10-17 Newcastle vs Man United
match.strDescriptionEN: Steve Bruce eyes back-to-back home victories as a stuttering Manchester United visits Newcastle United. Ole Gunnar Solskjaer's team struggled at St James' Park last year, with a late Matty Longstaff goal securing an unexpected win for the Magpies.

match.strFilename: English Premier League 2020-10-18 Crystal Palace vs Brighton
match.strDescriptionEN: Crystal Palace plays Brighton and Hove Albion in the first M23 Derby of 2020. Both teams shipped four goals in their last game before the international break, though Palace has already beaten Manchester United this season.

match.strFilename: English Premier League 2020-10-18 Leicester vs Aston Villa
match.strDescriptionEN: Returning to action for the first time since stunning defending champion Liverpool 7-2, Aston Villa heads on the road to face fellow in-form team Leicester City. The Foxes have a major scalp of their own this season after beating Manchester City 5-2.

match.strFilename: English Premier League 2020-10-18 Sheffield United vs Fulham
match.strDescriptionEN: Sheffield United looks to shake off its second season syndrome as it takes on fellow struggler Fulham. The visitor has dominated this fixture in recent times, winning the last three meetings including a 5-4 victory at Bramall Lane in 2017.

match.strFilename: English Premier League 2020-10-18 Tottenham vs West Ham
match.strDescriptionEN: Tottenham Hotspur Stadium hosts a London derby as West Ham United has the unenviable task of taking on a Spurs team that humiliated Manchester United last time out. The Hammers were the first road team to beat Spurs here, though, in 2019.

match.strFilename: English Premier League 2020-10-19 Leeds vs Wolves
match.strDescriptionEN: Leeds United’s return to the Premier League has brought huge excitement, with Marcelo Bielsa producing positive results and performances. Having held Manchester City to a 1-1 draw last time out, can Leeds now see off Wolverhampton Wanderers?

match.strFilename: English Premier League 2020-10-19 West Brom vs Burnley
match.strDescriptionEN: West Bromwich Albion's return to the Premier League has been tough going so far, with just one point from its opening four matches. Can Slaven Bilic's team kickstart its season as fellow struggler Burnley comes to town?

match.strFilename: English Premier League 2020-10-23 Aston Villa vs Leeds
English Premier League 2020-10-24 Fulham vs Crystal Palace
match.strDescriptionEN: Roy Hodgson takes Crystal Palace on a short trip across London to face newly-promoted Fulham. Scott Parker's side has struggled to re-acclimatize to life in the Premier League, without a point in its first four games.

match.strFilename: English Premier League 2020-10-24 Liverpool vs Sheffield United
match.strDescriptionEN: Reigning champion Liverpool takes on a side which gave it plenty of problems last season in Sheffield United. Although Liverpool came away from these fixtures last year with six points, the Blades acquitted themselves well against the champion.

match.strFilename: English Premier League 2020-10-24 Man United vs Chelsea
match.strDescriptionEN: Manchester United and Chelsea square off as two of the Premier League's biggest teams go head-to-head once again. Chelsea's big-money signings are yet to start paying off, as the likes of Timo Werner struggle to adapt to the English game.

match.strFilename: English Premier League 2020-10-24 West Ham vs Man City
match.strDescriptionEN: Manchester City travels to the London Stadium to take on a West Ham United side which has started the season better than any of its fans could have expected. Pep Guardiola's side, meanwhile, has yet to hit top gear in the Premier League this season.
